Author: lukechilds#2707

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but it really has nothing to do with anything other than what is displayed locally

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: as in, you can do a swap without ever having created an orderbook

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: there is a network

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: you submit a request to

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if a bob sees it and it is a swap he is configured to do, he will respond back

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: these initial responses include the specific txids being swapped

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so there is no need to get a compleete list of utxo of all nodes propagated to all other nodes (bad idea to do that)
